<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>252353</id>
    <title>Popup does not open while holding CTRL</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">This is the main page to the US HSBC website.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">You highlight Personal Internet
Banking on the upper right, and click Log-In.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">This uses a javascript to pop up
a new window for the log in page.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">Unfortunately, when you hold down Ctrl, the
page does not work correctly.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">It opens a new tab, but never displays a page in
the new tab.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.6">Instead it simply shows (Untitled).</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.7">The status bar reads "Waiting
for us.hsbc.com...", but does not change no matter how long you wait.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.2">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">1 Go to http://us.hsbc.com/personal/personal_home_page.html</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">2 Highlight personal internet banking.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.5">3 Hold down the Ctrl key and left click on Log-In</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Actual Results:  
A blank tab opens up, but does not display a page.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">The status bar states that
it is connecting, but never gets beyond this.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Expected Results:  
Opened the page that normally pops up in the tab.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">If this cannot be done, it
should simply pop up as it normally would.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
